args:
The Rose Queen reveals a way to save Vania,
but before the prince can act, Chronos appears,
intent on stopping him. The two sides clash—
over Vania's fate, and that of their worlds.
Good. Hang on, Vania... Just a bit longer.
Did we really need to bring her with us?\nI can't help but think she'd be more\ncomfortable resting back at the Halidom.
I agree, but we've no way of knowing\nwhen or where Chronos might strike.
And if the Rose Queen will allow it, we\nmay be able to shelter Vania within the\nwood. That would be safer still.
For all the ＂forbidden＂ talk,\nthe place ain't all that scary so far...
Hey, what's that sweet smell?\nIs that...flowers?
We have entered the Queen's domain.\nBe on guard, my fellows.
Leave at once. This place is not for you to\ntread. Even the basest of creatures knows\nto keep well clear of thorns.
Some do call me by that name.
What purpose brings humans to my garden\nof briars? I trust it was not the honeyed\nscent of roses that led you here?
I heard you keep vigil over the vampires.\nIf so, we have dire need of your aid.
...I do not know who told you thus, but I\nsimply allowed their kind to reside in the\ndepths of my woods.
I pledged them no further protection.\nThe wee princess you bear is no exception.
But nor do I wish them any harm.\nAnd to see a flowerbud wither ere\nit blooms brings me no joy.
Speak. If your intentions do not sully this\nbeautiful place of peace, I may be moved\nto render my aid.
Of course! Thank you, Your Majesty!
...I see. An irony, that. For a meal of blood\nto cause the flame of a vampire's life to\ngutter out.
And all because I allowed myself to be\ndeceived by Chronos... Rose Queen, do\nyou know of any way to save her life?
I do. But though it be quite simple, I fear\nthere's little meaning in sharing it with\nyou.
Your blood is at war with hers inside her\nbody, and hers appears on the verge of a\nfinal defeat.
Should her blood as a vampire grow\nstronger, however, it may yet prevail.
And how might one strengthen a vampire's\nblood?
I suppose she might drink of her own\nblood.
I fear I fail to see the logic.
You mean we just draw blood from her\nand have her drink that? That's all it takes?
Do not misapprehend. Her blood as she is\nnow would grant no relief. It must be blood\nreplete with the strength of good health.
So...it's got to be blood taken when\nVania's healthy?

Well, how do we get THAT? Go back in
time to before all this happened and ask
to borrow a cup like a neighbor needing
sugar?
Yes. Were it possible, that would be the\nideal solution.
Oh, come on! I mean, technically,\nI guess we DO know a guy, but...
Another cruel irony that the one who holds\nthe power we need most should be the foe\nwho incited this crisis.
Oh, my slippery-minded companions! Are\nyou perhaps forgetting that another who\nholds the power to stride causality exists?
The winds I wield are wings fit to soar\no'er the walls of time. I shall gladly,\nuh—flap them?—for the princess's sake!
Sooo... That means we can help Vania?
It does indeed. Though I fear I cannot ferry\nyou through time with me, I shall go now\nto see her in the past.
Her death would distort causality's flow.\nTo right such deviations is my sworn duty.
So, such a method did exist. It seems\nmy attentions were well-spent monitoring\nyour activities.
You have to be kidding me...!
Chronos! Rgh, we were followed here?!
I had intended to wait for an opportune\nmoment to strike the vampire princess\ndown... But the situation has changed.
I now see that you must be dealt with first,\nTuner.
Hah. This war-god's might transcends time\nitself. You will soon regret standing before\nthe unrelenting scythe of my gales!
Wait, Grimnir! Leave this fight to us.
We don't understand Vania's condition well\nenough to afford any delay. Go now, and\nget the blood she needs.
We'll stop Chronos here, whatever it takes!
You truly believe that possible, vessel? It\nseems I have been grossly underestimated,\nfor you to face me without his aid.
You would do well not to underestimate us\nin turn, wyrm.
Seriously. You think we can't keep you\nbusy here while he runs a quick errand?
You heard the man. Off ya go, Grimnir!
Please, Grimnir! You're her only hope!
Oh man... Ohhh man, this is getting so\ngood... I LOVE STUFF LIKE THIS!
Worry not, my diminutive friend. For I am\nthe god of war, that racing gale upon the\nfields of battle! None can match my speed!
I shall see my task done in the blink of an\neye!
I'll not allow you to do as you please,\nTuner.
That's our line, Chronos!\nAll your schemes unravel here!
Fool... To the very end, you insist on\nstanding in the way of my liege's works.
As you are a suitable vessel, I had\nhesitated to erase you from the scope\nof time...but I now see I have no choice.
Vanish forever beyond the bounds of this\nand all realities!
